-- Hungary Stocks: OTP, Mol, Egis, Raba Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-05T15:21:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-05/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-refiner-mol-are-active-in-budapest.html
     April 5 (Bloomberg) --Hungary’s benchmark BUX stock index
climbed 0.2 percent to 18,203.20 as of the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active equities in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  , Hungary’s largest refiner, gained as
much as 1.4 percent and last traded 0.3 percent stronger at
17,800 forint. Oil increased for the first time in three days as
claims for U.S. unemployment benefits dropped to a four-year low
and equities advanced, raising hopes that demand in the world’s
biggest user of oil will increase.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, snapped
a four-day losing streak, closing 0.5 percent higher at 3,750
forint. OTP proposed to pay a dividend for the 2011 fiscal year
at 100 percent of the face value of shares, the company said in
a statement to the Budapest Stock Exchange today.  Raba Nyrt. (RABA)  , a Hungarian vehicle and vehicle parts
maker, rallied 0.6 percent to 730 forint after winning an order
to supply seat frames and covers for Suzuki Motor Corp.  Egis Gyogyszergyar Nyrt. (EGIS)  , a Hungarian drugmaker
owned by Laboratoires Servier, advanced 3.8 percent to 14,950
forint. Concorde Ertekpapir Zrt. raised its recommendation for
the stock to overweight from equalweight.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
